The paper deals with distance functions in computational geometry, which is a central topic in cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the use of probability measures, which is a topic in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
